						<summary>

						<p>Two Slabs lying in the Pañchaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya II, 1440 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly engraved record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1364 (current), Raudri Āshaḍha śu. 1, Tuesday.</hi> The cyclic year given corresponds to Śaka 1362 (1363 current), when the details agree with <hi rend="bold">1440, A.D., May 31.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of provisions to a feeding house for feeding brāhmaṇas by Rāmarasa who was governing Kaḍaba-rājya. It states that <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇappa</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Maṅgaḷūru-rājyas,</hi> under the orders of <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Achaṇṇa-daṇṇāyaka.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
